Package io.github.joblo2213.sma.speedwire.protocol.telegrams

Class Telegram

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.joblo2213.sma.speedwire.protocol.telegrams.Telegram
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DiscoveryResponse, EnergyMeterTelegram
    public class Telegram
extends Object
    Data received via speedwire is called telegram.
    On construction of a telegram the data is validated and parsed.

    • Method Detail

      • from

        public static Telegram from​(DatagramPacket packet)
                     throws TelegramInvalidException

        Parses the given datagram packet into a telegram
        The returned telegram will be of a specific subclass if the data from the packet matches the subclasses requirements.

        Currently implemented subclasses:
        DiscoveryResponse, EnergyMeterTelegram

        Parameters:
        packet - packet that should be parsed as speedwire telegram
        Returns:
        parsed telegram
        Throws:
        TelegramInvalidException - if the packet is not a valid telegram

                 throws TelegramInvalidException,

        Validates the integrity of the telegram and throws an exception otherwise
        Throws:
        TelegramInvalidException - if the telegram data does violate the required data format

      • getByte

        public byte getByte​(int index)

        Returns the raw value from the specified position of the telegrams data

        Telegrams contain unsigned bytes while java byte is signed.
        It's in most cases better to use getUnsigned(int)!

        Parameters:
        index - index of the byte to return
        Returns:
        the value at the given position as signed byte

      • getBytes

        public byte[] getBytes​(int index,
                       int length)

        Returns an array of multiple bytes from the telegrams data

        Telegrams contain unsigned bytes while java byte is signed.
        It's in most cases better to use getUnsigned(int, int)!

        Parameters:
        index - index of the first byte to return
        length - size of the array to return
        Returns:
        an array containing a copy of the telegram data with the given range as signed bytes
